title: PPPP’s Ali Hassan wins PS-41 seat
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Candidate of Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) Ali Hassan has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-41 Sanghar-II constituency by securing 63,750 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Qazi Shams-ud-Din of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged 62,118 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 54.96 per cent.
